    "endDate": "2026-07-19T14:00:00+05:30",
    "description": "<h2>Meet the Maker: Taro Collective | SHOWCASE 02: Viewpoint \ud83d\udc41\ufe0f</h2><p>Join us for the latest session of our <strong>\u2018Meet the Maker\u2019</strong> series, part of <strong>SHOWCASE 02: Viewpoint</strong>.</p><p>This Sunday, we are hosting <strong>Taro Collective</strong>, a Bangalore and <strong>Milan-based furniture</strong> brand founded by Federico Fraternale, Marco Grimandi, and Shikha Rentala. Recipients of the prestigious Godrej Design Lab Fellowship 2025, the founders also run a multidisciplinary studio practice spanning interiors, temporary spaces, and brand-led environments. Their distinctive work seamlessly bridges Italian design thinking and engineering with Indian contexts, production, and ways of living.</p><p>This conversation will trace the making of Taro Collective through the idea of home, the movement of objects, and the core questions that continue to shape the brand. <strong>The founders will dive into their work across different cities and clients, the realities of building a design-led business, their relationship with the wider design community, and the unique way Taro Collective approaches product, process, and place.</strong> \ud83e\ude91\ud83d\udee0\ufe0f</p><p><em>Come with your questions\u2014the session will conclude with an open Q&amp;A.</em></p><h3>Event Details</h3><ul><li><p><strong>Date:</strong> Sunday, 19th July 2026</p></li><li><p><strong>Time:</strong> 11:50 PM \u2013 2:00 PM IST <em>(Please arrive 10 minutes early so we can get everyone seated smoothly!)</em></p></li><li><p><strong>Location:</strong> General Items, Ulsoor</p></li></ul><h3><strong>How to Book</strong></h3><p>Spaces are limited. Secure your spot by clicking the <strong>Book Now</strong> / <strong>Get Tickets</strong> button above. \ud83c\udf9f\ufe0f</p>",
